<br>
If religion is to be important, it should mean SOMETHING.  Oh, and give the cats some god choices!  Is there any reason the Vah Shir should be forsaken by the Gods?<br>
<br>
For quests - how about religious based Epics?  A second Epic quest that modifies your current Epic (or gives a different one, like the Tunare Pally Epic2) and gives Bane bonuses against the opponents of your deity.  For the agnostics, give them a quest for weapons that do nice stuff against all worshipers.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, do something about the hard epics (mage, warrior, enchanter) vs the easy epics (rogue, druid, shammy, cleric, etc).  It's absurd that some &quot;epics&quot; can be done literally in hours while others take months of waiting for a spawn and hoping you can get a kill before you get ks'd. <p>Hyardgune Varangian <BR> 57 Ogre Myrmidon of Gathered Might</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/upyrple.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pyrple</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/5/02 6:08:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=538.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Planes of Power Quests</span><hr size=1> I don't want a quest so I can choose a deity.  I'm proud to be an agnostic dark elf and I want to stay that way.<br>
