<br>
Well warriors aint exactly men of the cloth, they are hired swordsmen, barbarians and killers ... not nice people in general.  <br>
<br>
If you are a nice warrior then the liklihood is that your a paladin.  <br>
<br>
If you a hunter, and prefer the stealth attack your a ranger.  <br>
<br>
There are races that obviously would be diety aligned without question such as Dwarves.  <br>
<br>
With Half-Elves, they belong to no community neither hunmans nor elves and as such are half-breeds no belief in the gods.  As a half-elf (rp), I believe in my companions.<br>
<br>
So why should I be penalised for being an agnostic warrior when for all intensive purposes, I am selecting the religion which is aligned with my race.<br>
<br>
Don't I get penalised enough for having some of the worst starting stats and not having the benefit of immunity to front stunning.  Didnt have bash either, in fact one of the few benefits I did have that I was not KoS to practically anyone.   With the introduction of Velious, Luclin and PoP .. those benefits are now none existant. <br>
